In commemoration of the 73rd Republic Day for India, a reception was held at the Gujarati Sanskriti Kendra in Durban, making it the first of its kind since the start of the Covid pandemic. A reception lamp was lit by Consul General Anish Rajan together with respected dignitaries such as Council Speaker, Thabani Nyawose, the MEC for Economic Development and Tourism, Ravi Pillay, and MEC for Transport and Community Safety, Peggy Nkonyeni. It is was on this day in 1930 when India was declared independent from colonial rule. It was also on this day in 1965 when Hindi was declared as the official language of India.